#: ../../faq.rst:277
msgid ""
"then it is likely that your system has SELinux enabled and it is "
"preventing ZoneMinder from performaing certain activities. You then have "
"two choices. You can either tune SELinux to permit the required "
"operations or you can disable SELinux entirely which will permit "
"ZoneMinder to run unhindered. Disabling SELinux is usually performed by "
